Installation: {{meter value=30 min=0 max=100 label="30%"}}

Download: {{meter value=75 min=0 max=100 label="75%"}}

Processing: {{meter value=100 min=0 max=100 label="Complete"}}

== Progress Meter in Paragraphs

Current progress: {{meter value=60 min=0 max=100 label="60%"}}

Overall completion: {{meter value=85 min=0 max=100 label="85%"}}

== Progress Meter with Custom Range

{{meter value=5 min=1 max=20 text="1 to 20" label="Progress"}}

== Progress Meter Syntax

The progress meter object uses the format: `{{meter value=50 min=0 max=100 label="Progress"}}`

Where:
* `value` - Current value (default: 0)
* `min` - Minimum value (default: 0)
* `max` - Maximum value (default: 100)
* `label` - Optional label text
* `text` - Optional text content
* `id` - Optional ID attribute
